BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
The LCM of the denominators is [`21\text{,}`] so we start out by multiplying each side of the inequality by [`21\text{.}`]

[```\newcommand{\secondhighlight}[1]{\mathchoice{\colorbox{lightemerald}{$\displaystyle #1$}}{\colorbox{lightemerald}{$\textstyle #1$}}{\colorbox{lightemerald}{$\scriptstyle #1$}}{\colorbox{lightemerald}{$\scriptscriptstyle #1$}}}\newcommand{\multiplyleft}[2][\cdot]{{\highlight{{#2#1{}}}}}\newcommand{\divideunder}[2]{\frac{#1}{{\highlight{{#2}}}}}\newcommand{\amp}{&}
\begin{aligned}
\frac{4}{7}-\frac{4}{3}x\amp\le\frac{2}{3}\\
\multiplyleft{21}\left(\frac{4}{7}-\frac{4}{3}x\right)\amp\le\multiplyleft{21}\left(\frac{2}{3}\right)\\
21\left(\frac{4}{7}\right)-21\left(\frac{4}{3}x\right)\amp\le21\left(\frac{2}{3}\right)\\
12-28x\amp\le14\\
-28x\amp\le2\\
\divideunder{-28x}{-28}\amp\secondhighlight{{}\ge{}}\divideunder{2}{-28}\\
x\amp\ge-\frac{1}{14}
\end{aligned}
```]

Note that when we divided each side of the inequality by [`-28\text{,}`] the inequality symbol reversed direction. The solution set in set-builder notation is [`\left\{x\mid x\ge-\frac{1}{14}\right\}\text{.}`] The solution set in interval notation is [`\left[-\frac{1}{14},\infty\right)\text{.}`]

END_PGML_SOLUTION

